				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, it's entirely possible we're reading too much into this and it was just the regional style of the time. Another very distinct example are the British platformers of the early 90s:<br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/vVi2GGd.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Lots of bright, chrome-shaded characters with cartoony proportions and no outlines. The Atari ST had fewer restrictions than the NES, but it saw the same amount of stylistic consistency between different artists. Simply put, without modern references like VG-Resource, all these artists could do is look to their contemporaries to learn how to translate designs into pixel art.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><div style="text-align:center"><a href="http://dragondeplatino.deviantart.com/" class="postlink">deviantART</a> | <a href="http://www.spriters-resource.com/submitter/DragonDePlatino/" class="postlink">Spriter&#39;s Resource</a></div></div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

